---
// src/pages/sms.astro
// SMS terms stub. A2P 10DLC carrier-mandated boilerplate plus our own.
// Final wording confirmed alongside the Twilio + A2P registration.
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
---

<Legal title="SMS Terms" updatedAt="May 2026" description="How Dog Gone Clean uses SMS notifications.">
  <p>
    <em>This document is a draft. Final wording lands when the Twilio
    number and A2P 10DLC registration go live.</em>
  </p>

  <h2>What we send</h2>
  <p>
    If you opt in, Dog Gone Clean sends text messages tied to your
    Hurricane Bath service: appointment reminders three days out, one
    day out, and the morning of, a heads up text when we are on the
    way (with a live tracker link), and occasional service notices
    (card on file expiring, route changes that affect your visit).
  </p>

  <h2>Consent</h2>
  <p>
    By providing your mobile number during booking, you agree to
    receive these service related text messages. Consent is not a
    condition of any purchase.
  </p>

  <h2>Frequency</h2>
  <p>
    Message frequency varies with your service schedule. Recurring
    clients on a four week cadence will typically receive four to five
    messages per visit cycle.
  </p>

  <h2>Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Message and data rates may apply, set by your carrier. Dog Gone
    Clean does not charge for the messages.
  </p>

  <h2>HELP and STOP</h2>
  <p>
    Reply <strong>HELP</strong> at any time for help. Reply
    <strong>STOP</strong> at any time to opt out; you will receive a
    single confirmation message and no further messages from this
    number. You can opt back in later from the client portal.
  </p>

  <h2>Carriers</h2>
  <p>
    Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.
  </p>

  <h2>Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Your mobile number, SMS consent, and text message content are
    never shared with third parties for marketing.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about SMS: contact details land before launch.
  </p>
</Legal>
